$ Registry: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Office\_version_\Common\Graphics

{ DisableAnimations #reg-office-DisableAnimations

  When using the arrow key or `ctrl` + arrow key, the cursor glides over characters or words which I find a nuisance. This behaviour can be stopped by setting
 `DisableAnimations` to 1:
  gh|about-Windows-Registry|/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version/Common/Graphics/DisableAnimations.ps1||

}
